'I knew that little bear cubs can be overly excited, so I didn't have to wait long for them to start playing.'

The Kamchatka brown bear is a sub species of the brown bear, and is the largest sub species in Europe and Asia.

Despite their imposing size, these bears are generally not dangerous to humans, and only one per cent of encounters result in an attack. 

 

